A group, All For One, One For All, has thrown its weight behind the Member representing Wase Federal Constituency in plateau State, Hon. Ahmed Idris Wase, for the position of deputy speaker of the 9th NASS. In a statement issued in Jos, the group described Wase as the best candidate for deputy speaker because of his leadership qualities, experience and forthrightness. “He is an astute leader who is known as a man of simplicity, honesty, hard work and virtues which became visible since he came to limelight in 2005 as Executive Secretary of the Muslim Pilgrims Board and subsequently, as Member representing Wase Federal constituency from 2007 till date in the House of Representatives,” the group said.  …Youth group insists on Wase Why Wase deserves House Speakership NASS: Why I settled for dep speakership — Maje Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin